# Testing

Full strategy: `TESTING.md`.

## Baseline
- New public function → unit test (`test_<fn>_<scenario>`, AAA).
- Prefer focused pytest files over giant suites.
- Run relevant tests before claiming done.

```bash
pytest tests/test_<area>.py -v
# broader:
pytest tests/ -v -k "not integration and not smoke"
```

## Classifier / LLM changes
- Any change to classifier rules or LLM prompt → run eval:
  `venv/bin/python tools/eval_matching.py`
- Save/compare reports under `docs/eval/` when meaningful.
- Use skill `classifier-change`.

## Known noise
- Some poller tests may fail without Redis/async mocks — distinguish pre-existing from regressions.
- CI deselects hanging `test_session_ticker_transitions` — do not "fix" by re-enabling without investigation.
